\paragraph{\texorpdfstring{Overriding the Delimiters: \texttt{md},
\texttt{em}\hyperref[overriding-the-delimiters-md-em]{}}{Overriding the Delimiters: md, em}}\label{overriding-the-delimiters-md-em}

The final escape hatch, is to change the default Markdown and italics
delimiters from \VERB|\NormalTok{@}| and \VERB|\NormalTok{$}|
respectively, to something else.

Add the attribute
\VERB|\NormalTok{md}\OperatorTok{=\textless{}}\NormalTok{symbol}\OperatorTok{\textgreater{}\VerbBar{}}\NormalTok{none}|
to set the Markdown delimiter or disable, and
\VERB|\NormalTok{em}\OperatorTok{=\textless{}}\NormalTok{symbol}\OperatorTok{\textgreater{}\VerbBar{}}\NormalTok{none}|
to set the italics delimiter or disable.

Consider this \VERB|\NormalTok{bash}| example:

\begin{quote}
\textbf{Markdown Source}

\begin{Shaded}
\begin{Highlighting}[]
\NormalTok{\textasciigrave{}\textasciigrave{}\textasciigrave{}bash}
\NormalTok{rsync {-}av "$@" "deploy@$target:/srv/app/"}
\NormalTok{\textasciigrave{}\textasciigrave{}\textasciigrave{}}
\end{Highlighting}
\end{Shaded}

\textbf{Rendered Output}

\begin{Shaded}
\begin{Highlighting}[]
\FunctionTok{rsync} \AttributeTok{{-}av} \StringTok{"}\VariableTok{$@}\StringTok{"} \StringTok{"deploy@}\VariableTok{$target}\StringTok{:/srv/app/"}
\end{Highlighting}
\end{Shaded}
\end{quote}

If we want to bold the \VERB|\StringTok{"$@"}| for example, we need to
enable embedded Markdown. However, the two occurences each of
\VERB|\NormalTok{@}| and \VERB|\NormalTok{$}| make the default
delimiters (\VERB|\NormalTok{@}| and \VERB|\NormalTok{$}|) unusable. In
this example, we set the Markdown delimiter to be \VERB|\NormalTok{\%}|
instead, and disable the italics delimiter entirely.

\begin{quote}
\textbf{Markdown Source}

\begin{Shaded}
\begin{Highlighting}[]
\NormalTok{\textasciigrave{}\textasciigrave{}\textasciigrave{}bash \{md=\% em=none\}}
\NormalTok{rsync {-}av \%**"$@"**\% "deploy@$target:/srv/app/"}
\NormalTok{\textasciigrave{}\textasciigrave{}\textasciigrave{}}
\end{Highlighting}
\end{Shaded}

\textbf{Rendered Output}

\begin{Shaded}
\begin{Highlighting}[]
\FunctionTok{rsync} \AttributeTok{{-}av}\NormalTok{ \textbf{"\$@"} }\StringTok{"deploy@}\VariableTok{$target}\StringTok{:/srv/app/"}
\end{Highlighting}
\end{Shaded}
\end{quote}

{{{[} \emph{Note:} }Effectively,
\VERB|\OperatorTok{.}\NormalTok{embed\_md}| is
\VERB|\NormalTok{md=@ em=$}| and \VERB|\OperatorTok{.}\NormalTok{raw}|
is
\VERB|\NormalTok{md}\OperatorTok{=}\NormalTok{none em}\OperatorTok{=}\NormalTok{none}|.{ --- \emph{end note} {]}}}

\subsection{\texorpdfstring{Comparison
Tables\hyperref[comparison-tables]{}}{Comparison Tables}}\label{comparison-tables}

Comparison Tables are
\href{https://pandoc.org/MANUAL.html\#divs-and-spans}{fenced
\VERB|\NormalTok{Div}| blocks} that open with
\VERB|\OperatorTok{:::}\NormalTok{ cmptable}| and close with
\VERB|\OperatorTok{:::}|.
\href{https://pandoc.org/MANUAL.html\#fenced-code-blocks}{Fenced code
blocks} are the only elements that actually get added to Comparison
Tables, except that the last header (if any) before a
\href{https://pandoc.org/MANUAL.html\#fenced-code-blocks}{fenced code
block} is attached to the cell above.

\textbf{Markdown Source}

\begin{Shaded}
\begin{Highlighting}[]
\NormalTok{::: cmptable}
\FunctionTok{\#\#\# Before}
\InformationTok{\textasciigrave{}\textasciigrave{}\textasciigrave{}cpp}
\ControlFlowTok{switch} \OperatorTok{(}\NormalTok{x}\OperatorTok{)} \OperatorTok{\{}
  \ControlFlowTok{case} \DecValTok{0}\OperatorTok{:}\NormalTok{ std}\OperatorTok{::}\NormalTok{cout }\OperatorTok{\textless{}\textless{}} \StringTok{"got zero"}\OperatorTok{;} \ControlFlowTok{break}\OperatorTok{;}
  \ControlFlowTok{case} \DecValTok{1}\OperatorTok{:}\NormalTok{ std}\OperatorTok{::}\NormalTok{cout }\OperatorTok{\textless{}\textless{}} \StringTok{"got one"}\OperatorTok{;} \ControlFlowTok{break}\OperatorTok{;}
  \ControlFlowTok{default}\OperatorTok{:}\NormalTok{ std}\OperatorTok{::}\NormalTok{cout }\OperatorTok{\textless{}\textless{}} \StringTok{"don\textquotesingle{}t care"}\OperatorTok{;}
\OperatorTok{\}}
\InformationTok{\textasciigrave{}\textasciigrave{}\textasciigrave{}}

\FunctionTok{\#\#\# After}
\InformationTok{\textasciigrave{}\textasciigrave{}\textasciigrave{}cpp}
\NormalTok{x match }\OperatorTok{\{}
  \DecValTok{0} \OperatorTok{=\textgreater{}} \ControlFlowTok{do} \OperatorTok{\{}\NormalTok{ std}\OperatorTok{::}\NormalTok{cout }\OperatorTok{\textless{}\textless{}} \StringTok{"got zero"} \OperatorTok{\};}
  \DecValTok{1} \OperatorTok{=\textgreater{}} \ControlFlowTok{do} \OperatorTok{\{}\NormalTok{ std}\OperatorTok{::}\NormalTok{cout }\OperatorTok{\textless{}\textless{}} \StringTok{"got one"} \OperatorTok{\};}
\NormalTok{  \_ }\OperatorTok{=\textgreater{}} \ControlFlowTok{do} \OperatorTok{\{}\NormalTok{ std}\OperatorTok{::}\NormalTok{cout }\OperatorTok{\textless{}\textless{}} \StringTok{"don\textquotesingle{}t care"} \OperatorTok{\};}
\OperatorTok{\};}
\InformationTok{\textasciigrave{}\textasciigrave{}\textasciigrave{}}
\NormalTok{:::}
\end{Highlighting}
\end{Shaded}

